description: The parent company of Facebook, Instagram and WhatsApp said net profit in the third quarter was $15.7 billion – up 35% on the same period last year.
title: Facebook company Meta shows strong growth as AI spending surges

description: Russia and North Korea have deepened their political and military alliance as the Ukraine war has dragged on. Russia's President Vladimir Putin has not denied the deployment of North Korean troops to his country but has also refused to confirm it, while Russia's ambassador to the UN on Wednesday called them "mere assertions."
title: US and South Korea call for North Korea to withdraw troops from Russia

description: On October 25, singer Beyoncé came to support Kamala Harris at a rally in Houston. Before the Queen of Pop, a number of high-profile stars have tried to swing the race for the White House in their candidate's favor.
title: Beyoncé and Harris, Heston and Reagan, Sinatra and JFK ... the stars who support US presidential candidates

description: The torrential rains that swept through southeastern Spain from Tuesday evening to Wednesday killed at least 95 people. Many are still missing.
title: Around Valencia, almost a hundred dead in the 'floods of the century': 'The water came all at once, like a tsunami'

description: Eugene Rwamucyo's trial was the eighth in France relating to the genocide in 1994 when an estimated 800,000 people – mostly ethnic Tutsis – were slaughtered by the Hutu majority. The former doctor, 65, was found guilty of complicity in genocide, complicity in crimes against humanity and conspiring to prepare those crimes.
title: French court jails ex-doctor for role in Rwandan genocide

description: The Gomezes have lived in Douglas, a town on the border with Mexico, for over a century. Their rejection of immigration led them to support the Republican candidate.
title: In Arizona, this Latino family is switching to Trump after four generations of voting Democrat

description: British Treasury chief Rachel Reeves told lawmakers Wednesday that taxes will rise by £40 billion in order to plug a hole in the public finances and provide new funding for public services.
title: UK's Labour government hikes taxes in first budget

description: An advisory committee, led by France, has presented a roadmap designed to prevent these financial instruments, strongly criticized by some experts and nature conservation groups, from falling into the same pitfalls as carbon credits.
title: At COP 16, controversial 'biodiversity credits' are under discussion

description: Hundreds of undercover tankers ply the seas with flags of convenience and hidden owners, ensuring that Moscow maintains its oil revenues throughout its war with Ukraine.
title: Russia's ghost fleets, a strategic asset for selling sanctioned oil

description: Russian crude oil prices show that the effectiveness of sanctions against Moscow has diminished since the start of the war in Ukraine. Yet tightening them would entail risks for the global economy.
title: Why the impact of sanctions on Russian oil is weakening by the day

description: A migrant fell into the sea off the northern French coast on Wednesday morning, bringing the number of deaths this year linked to small boats to 57.
title: Man dies trying to cross the Channel, French authorities say

description: The Israeli army on Wednesday urged residents of Lebanon's main eastern city and surrounding villages to leave immediately, warning it was preparing attacks on Hezbollah targets.
title: Residents flee Lebanon's Baalbek after Israel issues evacuation warning

description: The Olympic and Paralympic Games contributed 0.4% to GDP growth in the third quarter of 2024, boosting consumption. However, economic activity outside the Olympics appears sluggish and concerning for 2025.
title: French economy sees small boost from the Olympics but outlook remains gloomy

description: Louis Aliot, the second-in-command of the far-right Rassemblement National party, gave a weak defense in court on Wednesday. Over 11 months, he only once called Laurent Salles, who was paid with EU funds to be his parliamentary assistant but in reality worked for the party's events division.
title: Former MEP's awkward defense at the French far right's fake jobs trial: 'It's a rather baroque procedure'

description: Amid the ongoing Israeli offensive on Lebanon, the Iran-aligned armed group has promoted its deputy secretary general to succeed Hassan Nasrallah, who was killed in an Israeli strike.
title: Hezbollah's new leader: Naim Kassem, the longtime deputy of Hassan Nasrallah

description: With just one week to go before the presidential election, the Democratic candidate chose Washington's Ellipse lawn for her final big rally, the same spot where Donald Trump harangued his supporters on January 6, 2021, before storming the Capitol.
title: Harris pits her restraint against 'petty tyrant' Trump in last major speech

description: During his first presidential campaign, the billionaire presented himself as a maverick at war with the 'elites.' But now, writes Le Monde columnist Gilles Paris, he is entrenched in a political and media system that could lead to the emergence of an oligarchy.
title: The Trump of 2024 is not the Trump of 2017

description: The French government, which is battling a major debt crisis, has predicted that the economy will grow by about 1% in 2024.
title: Paris Olympics helps French GDP to 0.4% rise in third quarter

description: Authorities reported on Tuesday that seven people were unaccounted for, six of them in the town of Letur, where a flash flood had invaded streets, swept away cars and flooded buildings.
title: Bodies found as torrential rains cause flash flooding in Spain

description: Le Monde reveals a large-scale system for circumventing sanctions on Moscow, orchestrated by several companies linked to Coral Energy, a company that works with France's Société Générale and TotalEnergies.
title: Shell companies, ghost ships and secret traders: How Russia circumvents Western oil sanctions

description: A vast judicial investigation is revealing the links between the 'Ndrangheta and the powerful ultras groups backing the city's two clubs, Internazionale and AC Milan.
title: The Calabrian mafia's hold on Milan's football stands

description: The Yankees pulled within 3-1 in the best-of-seven Major League Baseball championship showdown with game five on Wednesday at Yankee Stadium. No team has ever recovered from a 3-0 deficit to win the World Series.
title: New York Yankees crush Dodgers 11-4 to avoid World Series sweep by Los Angeles team

description: At Trump's Madison Square Garden rally on Sunday, comic Tony Hitchcliffe called Puerto Rico 'a floating island of garbage,' which has reverberated across the American voter landscape just a week before Election Day on November 5, fueling a group of passionate protesters to flock to Trump's Allentown, Pennsylvania rally on Tuesday.
title: 'Fuera!' Latinos protest Trump in battleground Pennsylvania city as US presidential election nears

description: In 2022, the Ukrainian city lived under Russian occupation for months, which claimed the lives of over 1,000 inhabitants.
title: War in Ukraine: Izium, the difficult rebirth of a martyred town

description: Amazon founder Jeff Bezos, owner of the American newspaper, is suspected of having blocked the editorial board's support for the Democratic candidate in the name of his own interests. This sudden choice of neutrality led to the desertion of 250,000 subscribers in four days.
title: 'Washington Post' in turmoil after refusing to endorse Harris or Trump

description: In an interview, the criminal lawyer specializing in women's rights and domestic violence compiles a typology of the different types of rape, from predatory to opportunistic and re-appropriatory, based on her own experience.
title: Lawyer Anne Bouillon: 'Opportunistic rape is much more common than you might think'

description: 'Look, we know who Donald Trump is. He is the person who stood at this very spot nearly four years ago and sent an armed mob to the United States Capitol to overturn the will of the people in a free and fair election," the Vice President said on Tuesday
title: US election: Kamala Harris promises to 'put country above party,' a 'direct contrast' to Trump in speech at symbolic site
